      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0584P0-03718'>
        <a name='S5LV0584P0_19980119_GCR_170'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-andrew-mcintosh' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0584P0_19980119_GCR_170' title='Link to this speech by Mr Andrew McIntosh' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-andrew-mcintosh" title="Mr Andrew McIntosh">Lord McIntosh of Haringey</a></cite>
          <p class='first-para'>
            I shall, of course, reflect on it, but it may be my fault that I was oversimplifying. The first three initiatives, which we have set out in some detail, are certainly national initiatives which include Scotland, and they have to be, but that is not to say that future initiatives for the new opportunities fund could not relate entirely to Scotland and be controlled entirely by the Scottish executive.</p><p>
